# PLUMED 2.9 single-walker WT-MetaD template for PfTrpS(Ain) TrpB benchmark
#
# ⚠️ DEPRECATED — DO NOT USE THIS TEMPLATE AS-IS (FP-022, 2026-04-08)
#
# This template predates FP-022 (path CV LAMBDA convention bug). It uses
# PATHMSD with LAMBDA=3.3910, which is wrong by factor N_atoms = 112.
# The PATHMSD path also failed for unrelated reasons (FP-020: PATHMSD does
# not handle non-sequential atom serials in multi-model PDB through mdrun).
#
# CORRECT TEMPLATE: see replication/metadynamics/single_walker/plumed.dat
# (uses FUNCPATHMSD + RMSD ... SQUARED + LAMBDA=379.77)
#
# OR: regenerate with replication/metadynamics/path_cv/generate_path_cv.py
# which now auto-emits a ready-to-use plumed_path_cv.dat snippet.
#
# This file is kept only for historical reference. See:
#   - replication/validations/2026-04-08_path_cv_lambda_bug.md
#   - replication/validations/failure-patterns.md (FP-022)
#
# Original (broken) content below for reference:
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# This is the pre-production validation input:
#   1. confirm PATHMSD wiring
#   2. confirm converted GROMACS atom indices
#   3. generate initial biased exploration before 10-walker launch
#
# Paper-aligned parameters:
#   - HEIGHT = 0.628 kJ/mol
#   - PACE = 1000
#   - BIASFACTOR = 10
#   - TEMP = 350 K
#   - adaptive Gaussian widths
#
# FP-004 guard:
#   Every atom index here must be extracted after AMBER->GROMACS conversion from
#   the final .gro/.tpr, not inferred from the source PDB or AMBER ordering.
#
# SIGMA=0.05 is the initial seed for ADAPTIVE=GEOM.
# PLUMED automatically adjusts Gaussian widths based on local CV fluctuations.
# This matches the SI protocol (adaptive Gaussian widths).

# ⚠️ FP-022: LAMBDA=3.3910 is WRONG (off by N_atoms=112). Use 379.77 with
# FUNCPATHMSD + SQUARED. Do NOT copy this line into a new plumed.dat.
path: PATHMSD REFERENCE=PLACEHOLDER_PENDING_CONVERSION_PATH_REFERENCE_PDB LAMBDA=3.3910  # ⚠️ DEPRECATED, see header

k82_q2: DISTANCE ATOMS=PLACEHOLDER_PENDING_CONVERSION_K82_NZ_Q2_C
e104_q2: DISTANCE ATOMS=PLACEHOLDER_PENDING_CONVERSION_E104_OE_Q2_C

# FP-019: all METAD parameters on one line (no backslash continuation for GROMACS 2026 compatibility)
metad: METAD ARG=path.sss,path.zzz SIGMA=0.05 ADAPTIVE=GEOM HEIGHT=0.628 PACE=1000 BIASFACTOR=10 TEMP=350 FILE=HILLS

PRINT ARG=path.sss,path.zzz,k82_q2,e104_q2,metad.bias FILE=COLVAR STRIDE=500
